			<h0><![CDATA[]]></h0>
			<h1><![CDATA[With Cursor Right (above in the Header), a window opens with a Graph-Viewer. It can be viewed all stored graphs.]]></h1>
			<h2><![CDATA[Rules for Entry Names (only available with enhanced recipes)
- The recipe name must not be empty.
- Each recipe entry must have a unique name.

The checking of the observance of these name rules is always carried out by the runtime before a recipe is saved. If the rules are not observed, an appropriate system error message will be generated to indicate this and the recipe cannot be saved.]]></h2>
			<h3><![CDATA[A help window is used to display the texts for a Help Button or the help texts of an error message. See section Error Text for information on defining help text for error messages.
Additionally in each Help Button you can choose a separate Helpmask.
Use this to define the font style, font size and color of the text contained in the Help window. The position and the size of the object determines also the position and size of the help window.

Only one help window can be defined for each mask, i.e. all help texts of a mask are displayed at the same position and with the same parameters (font style, font size, color etc.).
Since a help window can cover a large area of the screen many times (it is only temporarily visible) the view of the object can be switched on and off via the menu point Help Window in the View menu.]]></h3>
			<h4><![CDATA[Use this object to display any text in a Help Window on the MMI. A help text can be assigned to each help button. The Help window is only visible after a Help button has been pressed or the Error help function activated in conjunction with an  Error Window. Additionally in each Help Button you can choose a separate Helpmask. The Help window disappears again as soon as the MMI is touched.]]></h4>
			<h5><![CDATA[Helptext for the Tag  in Entry 0:

